1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,240
Hello everyone and welcome back to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:06,240
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:10,320
My name is Catherine and today we're talking about buying clothes.
我是Catherine，今天我们聊聊买衣服的事。

4
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:11,320
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:15,200
We're going to go and get some clothes but on this occasion, we're going to get a suit
我们要去买些衣服，但这次，我们要买一套西装，

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:18,000
and we're going to have it made especially for us.
而且是专门为我们定做的。

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,040
So before we get started, why don't we take a look at one keyword that we have in Vocabulary
所以在开始之前，我们先来看看词汇预览中的一个关键词。

8
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:24,320
Preview.
预览。

9
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:25,640
Vocabulary Preview.
词汇预览。

10
00:00:25,640 --> 00:00:31,280
Okay, this word makes me think of things that are very rich and soft.
好的，这个词让我想到非常奢华柔软的东西。

11
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:32,280
It's a fabric, right?
它是一种面料，对吧？

12
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,280
That's right.
没错。

13
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,280
It's a kind of textile.
它是一种纺织品。

14
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,280
It's called cashmere.
它叫羊绒。

15
00:00:35,280 --> 00:00:36,280
Cashmere.
羊绒。

16
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:38,520
So maybe you've heard of cashmere wool.
你可能听说过羊绒羊毛。

17
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:42,120
It's a special kind of wool that comes from animals.
它是一种来自动物的特殊羊毛。

18
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:48,840
So this is a textile or a fabric that is commonly used to make pants, nice pants or suits for
所以这是一种常用于制作裤子、高档裤子或男士西装的纺织品或面料。

19
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:49,840
men.
男士西装。

20
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:50,840
Or scars or sweaters.
或者围巾、毛衣。

21
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:55,760
If you've ever had a cashmere sweater, you know it's very luxurious, very soft.
如果你有过羊绒毛衣，就知道它非常奢华、非常柔软。

22
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:59,920
So it can be a little bit expensive depending on the quality and that's what we're going
所以根据质量不同，它可能有点贵，这就是我们现在要看的。

23
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:00,920
to be looking at now.
我们现在要看的。

24
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:04,200
We're going to be making a suit out of cashmere.
我们要用羊绒做一套西装。

25
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:12,600
So why don't we listen to our dialogue for the first time.
那么，我们先来听一遍对话。

26
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:13,960
Welcome to Bill's Fabric World.
欢迎来到比尔面料世界。

27
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:15,440
What can I do for you today?
今天我能为您做些什么？

28
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:18,720
I was wondering if you guys also tailor clothes.
我想问一下你们这里也做衣服裁剪吗？

29
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:19,720
Sure we do.
当然做。

30
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:21,360
We're the best tailors in the country.
我们是全国最好的裁缝。

31
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:23,400
What is it that you need exactly?
您具体需要什么？

32
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:26,240
Well I'm looking to get a custom made suit.
嗯，我想定做一套西装。

33
00:01:26,240 --> 00:01:27,240
Excellent.
太好了。

34
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:29,760
We have the finest cashmeres at affordable prices.
我们有最优质的羊绒，价格实惠。

35
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:31,200
How about we get you measured?
我们先给您量一下尺寸吧？

36
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:36,240
Let's start off by measuring the width of your shoulders.
先从量您的肩宽开始。

37
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:41,100
Now let's measure the length of your arms and this bit around your neck here.
现在量一下您的臂长和脖子这里。

38
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:44,360
Can you make sure you leave a little extra space in the collar?
您能确保在领口留点多余空间吗？

39
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:46,600
My neck gets easily irritated.
我的脖子容易不舒服。

40
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:47,600
No problem.
没问题。

41
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:52,560
Now for your pants, let me just measure your waist and the inseam.
现在量您的裤子，让我量一下您的腰围和内缝长。

42
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:55,560
You might also want to leave a little extra room in the waist area.
您可能也想在腰部留点多余空间。

43
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:58,520
I tend to gain a few pounds over the holidays.
我假期容易长几斤肉。

44
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,520
Okay.
好的。

45
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,760
Now you can pick your fabric and pattern design.
现在您可以挑选面料和图案设计了。

46
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:06,360
Please follow me.
请跟我来。

47
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:10,880
So this reminds me of something that people used to do a lot more often.
这让我想起以前人们更常做的事。

48
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:14,480
So you'd go to the tailor and you'd have some clothes made.
就是去裁缝那里定做衣服。

49
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,160
Most people don't do this anymore.
现在大多数人都不这么做了。

50
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,160
Yeah.
是啊。

51
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,960
It's actually really interesting.
其实挺有意思的。

52
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:22,640
Maybe because it's more expensive nowadays or tailors are harder to find.
可能是因为现在更贵了，或者裁缝更难找了。

53
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:23,640
That's right.
没错。

54
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:27,440
So let's learn about the words first and what they mean and then maybe we can talk about
所以先学学这些词的意思，然后也许我们可以在节目最后聊聊这个。

55
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:31,480
this at the end of today's show.
节目最后。

56
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:32,480
Language takeaway.
语言要点。

57
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:37,520
Alright, so today on language takeaway we have a word that is a noun and a verb.
好的，今天在语言要点里，我们有一个既是名词又是动词的词。

58
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:41,160
So as you mentioned, the person that makes suits is a tailor.
就像你提到的，做西装的人是裁缝。

59
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:42,160
That's right.
没错。

60
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,040
You can say, my uncle is a tailor.
你可以说，我叔叔是个裁缝。

61
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:47,280
He makes clothes for famous people.
他为名人做衣服。

62
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:49,780
But this word is also a verb.
但这个词也是动词。

63
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:51,120
That means it's an action word.
意思是它是一个动作词。

64
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:56,000
We can say, my uncle the tailor, he tailors clothes.
我们可以说，我叔叔那个裁缝，他裁剪衣服。

65
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,560
Okay, so to tailor clothes.
好的，所以是裁剪衣服。

66
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,200
And what does it mean when you say to tailor?
那你说“裁剪”是什么意思呢？

67
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,400
Well, it can have two meanings.
嗯，它有两个意思。

68
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,800
The first is what we learn about in today's dialogue.
第一个是我们在今天对话中学到的。

69
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,360
It means to make clothes.
意思是做衣服。

70
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:09,760
So to make a shirt or to make a pair of pants.
比如做衬衫或做裤子。

71
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:13,960
But these days we often say to tailor which means to fix something.
但现在我们常说“裁剪”，意思是修改东西。

72
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:19,320
So for example, Marco, if you buy a pair of pants and they're too long, you can have them
比如，Marco，如果你买了一条裤子太长，你可以拿去改。

73
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:20,320
tailored.
拿去改。

74
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,320
Have them tailored.
拿去改。

75
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:25,080
And that means that I am going to have them fixed so they fit me properly.
这意味着我要把它们修改得合身。

76
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,080
Exactly.
没错。

77
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,680
This is a lot more common right now.
现在这更常见了。

78
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:29,880
Okay, so we're going to be tailoring clothes.
好的，所以我们要裁剪衣服。

79
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:34,800
Now if any of you have ever been to the tailor, what they do is they measure you.
如果你们谁去过裁缝店，他们会给你量尺寸。

80
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,800
And what do they measure?
他们量什么呢？

81
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:39,720
Well, in this case, they get the width of your shoulders.
嗯，在这种情况下，他们量的是你肩膀的宽度。

82
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:43,800
What's really great about these upcoming words is that they're useful in math as well.
这些即将学到的词很棒，因为它们在数学里也很有用。

83
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,840
Math and basic measurements.
数学和基本测量。

84
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:51,800
So width is how big something is across.
所以宽度是指某物横向有多大。

85
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,360
How wide something is.
某物有多宽。

86
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,360
Exactly.
没错。

87
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,360
Wide, width.
宽，宽度。

88
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,680
Okay, so that's the width.
好的，那就是宽度。

89
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:59,440
Now your shoulders, they are wide.
现在你的肩膀，它们很宽。

90
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:03,640
And well, your legs on the other hand, your legs and arms, you don't measure the width
而另一方面，你的腿，你的腿和胳膊，通常不量宽度，

91
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,560
usually, you measure the length.
而是量长度。

92
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:07,200
How long they are.
它们有多长。

93
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,240
Okay, so width and length.
好的，所以是宽度和长度。

94
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:12,800
Now just to throw it in there, this wasn't in the dialogue, but what would be the other
现在顺便提一下，对话里没提到，但另一个

95
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,800
measure word?
测量词是什么？

96
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,280
So the third word would be height.
第三个词是高度。

97
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:21,440
So you think of a rectangle, you have the width, how wide something is, the length,
所以想象一个长方形，你有宽度，即某物有多宽；长度，

98
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:23,840
how long it is, and the height, how tall it is.
即它有多长；以及高度，即它有多高。

99
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:25,160
How tall it is, right.
它有多高，对。

100
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,640
So width, length, and height.
所以是宽度、长度和高度。

101
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,640
All right.
好的。

102
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:31,800
Now that we've measured our arms and legs, now we want to measure our waist.
现在我们量完了胳膊和腿，接下来要量腰围。

103
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,960
Okay, this is the important one.
好的，这是重要的一项。

104
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,640
This is also the sensitive one.
这也是敏感的一项。

105
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:39,280
If you find that you've gained some weight, we measure the waist.
如果你发现自己胖了，我们就量腰围。

106
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:42,480
Okay, that's how big you are around your stomach.
好的，那是你肚子周围有多大。

107
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,800
And so usually we measure this in a circle.
通常我们绕着圈量。

108
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:50,240
Okay, so you've heard of a 26 inch waist or a 32 inch waist.
好的，所以你听说过26英寸腰围或32英寸腰围。

109
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,760
This is the size of your stomach.
这是你肚子的大小。

110
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:54,600
Okay, so it's just above your hips, right?
好的，就在臀部上方，对吧？

111
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,680
As you say, it's your stomach.
就像你说的，是你的肚子。

112
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,760
And well, we've measured the waist.
嗯，我们量了腰围。

113
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:02,120
And now in men especially, they measure the inseam.
现在尤其是男士，他们会量内缝长。

114
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:05,280
Now this is very particular for tailors and having suits made.
这对裁缝和定制西装来说非常特别。

115
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,320
What is the inseam of your pants?
你裤子的内缝长是多少？

116
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,440
Well think of the word in, inside.
想想“内”这个词，内部。

117
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:12,080
This is the inside of your pants.
这是你裤子的内侧。

118
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:17,520
So from your foot to the middle of your pants where your zipper starts.
所以从你的脚到裤子中间拉链开始的地方。

119
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:22,560
So that's not the outside length, it's the inside length.
所以那不是外侧长度，而是内侧长度。

120
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:25,800
Now for example, skirts, they don't have inseams, right?
比如，裙子就没有内缝长，对吧？

121
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:29,120
No, because there's no inside, there's no middle.
没有，因为没有内侧，没有中间。

122
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,200
So it's just like a circle.
所以它就像一个圆圈。

123
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:34,480
But in pants or shorts, you have an inseam.
但在裤子或短裤里，你有内缝长。

124
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,560
That's where it's connected in the middle.
那是它们在中间连接的地方。

125
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,840
All right, so also in shorts, very interesting.
好的，短裤也一样，很有趣。

126
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:42,360
So you can measure the inseam of pants or shorts.
所以你可以量裤子或短裤的内缝长。

127
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:45,880
All right, so very interesting and particular words for tailors.
好的，这些词对裁缝来说非常有趣和特别。

128
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:53,480
Why don't we listen to our dialogue again and we'll be back shortly.
我们再来听一遍对话，一会儿回来。

129
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,840
Welcome to Bill's Fabric World.
欢迎来到比尔布料世界。

130
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,360
What can I do for you today?
今天我能为您做些什么？

131
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:59,600
I was wondering if you guys also tailor clothes.
我想知道你们是否也做衣服修改。

132
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,600
Sure we do.
当然可以。

133
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,240
We have the best tailors in the country.
我们有全国最好的裁缝。

134
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,760
What is it that you need exactly?
您具体需要什么？

135
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:07,120
Well, I'm looking to get a custom made suit.
嗯，我想定制一套西装。

136
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:08,120
Excellent.
太好了。

137
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,680
We have the finest cashmeres at affordable prices.
我们有最优质的羊绒，价格实惠。

138
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,120
How about we get you measured?
我们先给您量尺寸吧？

139
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:14,680
Let's start off by measuring the width of your shoulders.
我们先量一下您肩膀的宽度。

140
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:18,640
Now let's measure the length of your arms and this bit around your neck here.
现在量一下您胳膊的长度和脖子这里这一圈。

141
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:21,880
Can you make sure you leave a little extra space in the collar?
您能在领口留点额外空间吗？

142
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:24,120
My neck gets easily irritated.
我的脖子容易不舒服。

143
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,120
No problem.
没问题。

144
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:28,860
Now for your pants, let me just measure your waist and the inseam.
现在量您的裤子，让我量一下您的腰围和内缝长。

145
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:31,840
You might also want to leave a little extra room in the waist area.
您可能也想在腰部留点额外空间。

146
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:34,760
I tend to gain a few pounds over the holidays.
我假期容易胖几磅。

147
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,760
Okay.
好的。

148
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:38,040
Now you can pick your fabric and pattern design.
现在您可以挑选面料和图案设计了。

149
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:40,520
Please follow me.
请跟我来。

150
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:43,720
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

151
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:47,120
So now we have three key phrases that we found in this dialogue.
所以我们在对话中找到了三个关键短语。

152
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:51,680
So let's take a look at them now in Fluency Builder.
现在让我们在流利度构建器中看看它们。

153
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,980
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

154
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:56,200
This first phrase is the topic of today's lesson.
第一个短语是今天课程的主题。

155
00:06:56,200 --> 00:07:01,600
We talked a little bit about measurements for a suit, but in particular we're getting
我们聊了一点西装的测量，但特别提到了

156
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,720
a custom made suit.
定制西装。

157
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,720
Okay.
好的。

158
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,360
So this word custom made.
所以这个词“定制”。

159
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:10,040
Well, custom is important, it means special or unique.
嗯，“定制”很重要，意思是特别或独特。

160
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,240
There's no other like it.
没有其他一样的。

161
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,240
So we could talk about custom cars.
所以我们可以聊聊定制车。

162
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:16,120
That means a car that has been fixed especially for you.
那是指一辆专门为你改装的车。

163
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,120
Okay.
好的。

164
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:22,000
So a custom made suit would be a suit that was made specifically for your height, for
所以一套定制西装就是根据你的身高、

165
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,400
how big your waist is, etc.
腰围等量身定做的西装。

166
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,400
Specifically for you.
专门为你做的。

167
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,400
Right.
对。

